The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Hyderabad: Three persons were killed on Friday in a mad rush for tickets for Chiranjeevis latest blockbuster Stalin.

 Ananthpur, an 18-year-old boy was crushed to death at a cinema, while a 16-year-old girl committed suicide after she failed to get tickets for a first-day show. The third victim was a housewife from Karimnagar, who slipped from a railing she was trying to climb to get ahead of the serpentine queue at the ticket counter.

 The politically-charged film, which has been receiving rave reviews, portrays the 55-year-old southern superstar as a good Samaritan.

 Hyderabad: The Telengana Rastra Samiti has withdrawn its support to Manmohan Singhs government. In a letter to the President on Saturday, TRS chief and former Union minister K. Chandrasekhar Rao charged the UPA with failing to keep its promise to facilitate formation of a separate state of Telengana.

 Chennai (PTI): A man has been arrested at Chennai airport while trying to pass off restricted VHF transceivers and similar items as cameras, directorate of revenue intelligence officials said. The items included marine communication equipment like marine transceivers, and navigators worth Rs 11 lakh.




